  schema:url &lt;https://emsenn.net/library/domains/engineering/domains/domesticity/domains/production/gardening/terms/malabar-spinach/> ;
  schema:name "Malabar spinach cultivation" ;
  schema:description "Growing protocol for *Basella rubra*, vigorous tropical vine from India's Malabar Coast. Requires warmth (minimum 20°C, optimal 25–35°C) and humidity; unsuitable for temperate field cultivation but thrives in greenhouses, warm regions, and container culture. Produces succulent, heart-shaped leaves and edible red berries. Twines 3–6 meters per season; excellent vertical production system." ;
